      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey can u help me with a depreciation problem for my accounting class? i need to find the annual depreciation for a machine that cost 50000 but has a salvage value of 5000 and a useful life of 5 years. can u show the formula and how u get the answer?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Of course, I can help you with that! To find the annual depreciation, we first need to calculate the depreciable cost, which is the total cost minus the salvage value. The formula for straight-line depreciation is: (Cost - Salvage Value) / Useful Life.\n\nPlugging in your numbers: (50,000 - 5,000) / 5 = 45,000 / 5 = 9,000.\n\nSo, the annual depreciation for your machine is **9,000**.\n\nLet me know if you need help with any other accounting problems!",
